  <span id="freeText10778092240718874471" style="display:none">This is a great book with a wonderful flow to it. I would say it’s an everyday read for any occasion. The design of the little bird must have a little to do with this. I feel Germany Kent took great care to only add quotes that allows you to be uplifted. They’re not consume on the things you should have done, but the things you can. Nor of what someone else thinks of you, but how you must think of yourself. <br /><br />It’s all for you, your happiness, your growth, and what you can do for yourself. All the quotes are free flowing, helpful, and each quote guides you into the next. I feel "The Hope Handbook" will be a great and useful everyday read for many. <br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
