<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer5125364826492790059">Germany Kent is an American Hall of Fame media and communications professional, bestselling author, national award-winning producer, broadcast and digital journalist, activist and philanthropist. Kent has been spotlighted in national and international media. She has appeared across all mediums (TV, radio, print, online), and has been profiled as a national authority featured, interviewed, or quote</span>
  <span id="freeText5125364826492790059" style="display:none">Germany Kent is an American Hall of Fame media and communications professional, bestselling author, national award-winning producer, broadcast and digital journalist, activist and philanthropist. Kent has been spotlighted in national and international media. She has appeared across all mediums (TV, radio, print, online), and has been profiled as a national authority featured, interviewed, or quoted in Fast Company, Inc., Huffpost, Bloomberg Business, Cosmopolitan, Hartford Business, Yahoo, Herald Tribune, MSN, The Dallas Morning News, and Forbes, to name a few. Guest features on national radio and TV include: NPR, Money Matters Radio, iHeartRadio, Gnet Radio, Voice America, the CW, CBS, NBC, ABC and FOX News. As an accomplished executive producer, reporter, writer and former FOX News evening anchor, Kent has experience in front of and behind the camera. The multi-skilled journalist and entertainment host has interviewed hundreds of prominent newsmakers, athletes, politicians, and celebrities. Kent is a noted advocate for youth empowerment, anti-bullying/cyberbullying activist, and has become a well-respected voice for online etiquette and digital branding. Kent's influence and outreach efforts have apparently garnered her a host of fans as she is broadly and frequently quoted on the Web by individuals and organizations all over the world. The thought leader and media scholar is an alumna of Mississippi State University, University of Alabama, and the University of Southern California. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5125364826492790059" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
